text: Anas Mustafa (born 20 May 2000) is a Pakistani cricketer. He made his List A debut for Zarai Taraqiati Bank Limited in the 2018–19 Quaid-e-Azam One Day Cup on 6 September 2018. He made his first-class debut for Zarai Taraqiati Bank Limited in the 2018–19 Quaid-e-Azam Trophy on 8 September 2018. He was the leading run-scorer for Zarai Taraqiati Bank Limited in the tournament, with 385 runs in six matches. ==References== ==External links== * Category:2000 births Category:Living people Category:Pakistani cricketers Category:Zarai Taraqiati Bank Limited cricketers Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Southern Punjab (Pakistan) cricketers
